description._content: Catalog #: 09_01645 Title: First Lieutenant Harry Haw Special Collection Photo Webster South Dakota Additional Information: De Havilland DH-4 aircraft crash in hay field. Handwritten inscription ""Harry piled up the plane in a straw stack. No one hurt"", Harry Haw served in the U.S. Army in the 514th Observation Squadron. He entered the U.S. Army in 1917 and became a First Lieutenant in 1930. He became a civilian Transport Pilot by 1930 and had logged 789 flying hours by 1934. he later became Principal of the Alice Birney school.
